34:36.350 --> 34:39.380
It was a crisis that
everybody found a need,

34:39.380 --> 34:40.880
and everybody helped.

34:40.880 --> 34:41.949
- [Gordon] Yeah, except them.

34:41.949 --> 34:42.783
- Except them.

34:42.783 --> 34:44.213
- But that's the spirit
of Chelan, I think,

34:44.213 --> 34:45.739
is what we're getting at.

34:45.739 --> 34:49.210
We share tractors, we share,
you know, from vineyard work,

34:49.210 --> 34:51.650
some of us have restaurants,
so we share employees.

34:51.650 --> 34:52.713
- He's oblivious.

34:54.949 --> 34:56.179
How come there's no wine

34:57.030 --> 34:59.350
from this amazing region on their list?

34:59.350 --> 35:01.320
- When we first started our winery,

35:01.320 --> 35:05.110
his excuse was that the
wineries have restaurants

35:05.110 --> 35:07.990
that compete with his restaurant.

35:07.990 --> 35:08.823
- In addition to that,

35:08.823 --> 35:11.570
it would be a shame if there
was just one good place

35:11.570 --> 35:12.830
in town to go to.

35:12.830 --> 35:14.570
We want tourists to come here

35:14.570 --> 35:16.820
and have a great time everywhere they go.

35:16.820 --> 35:19.423
So if he does well, we'll all do well.

35:20.400 --> 35:22.650
- I really appreciate the feedback.

35:22.650 --> 35:25.540
But I want you to help me get through

35:25.540 --> 35:28.540
to them on another level now,
because I'm gonna go get them.

35:30.946 --> 35:32.746
And we're gonna tackle this head on.

35:33.790 --> 35:36.082
Give me two minutes, thank you so much.

35:36.082 --> 35:37.120
- You wanna go?

35:37.120 --> 35:39.060
It's really, really hard to take it.

35:39.060 --> 35:39.893
- Let's go.

35:39.893 --> 35:42.180
- Because we try really hard.

35:42.180 --> 35:43.320
It just shocked me.

35:43.320 --> 35:44.153
Wow.

35:45.983 --> 35:47.460
- Hi.
- Hi, folks.

35:47.460 --> 35:49.313
- These are, in my mind,

35:50.570 --> 35:51.840
even more important than the customers,

35:51.840 --> 35:53.743
because you guys should be bonding.

35:55.210 --> 35:56.210
Clearly, you're not.

35:57.660 --> 35:59.910
Why's it taken so long?

35:59.910 --> 36:03.433
- Sometimes you need somebody
just to slap your face.

36:06.360 --> 36:08.793
- We were in a comfort zone somewhat.

36:10.220 --> 36:13.780
And used to the way we
did everything, you know,

36:13.780 --> 36:16.990
for a lot of years, and
it needs to be changed.

36:16.990 --> 36:19.443
Maybe we banked on the location too much.

36:20.570 --> 36:22.560
There's a lot of things we've done wrong.

36:22.560 --> 36:24.140
- [Gordon] They're desperate
to see you do well.

36:24.140 --> 36:25.110
Anything to say?

36:25.110 --> 36:27.793
- There can never be too many fun,

36:28.680 --> 36:30.440
good places in town.

36:30.440 --> 36:33.510
We always want somewhere to go and relax

36:33.510 --> 36:34.900
and enjoy ourselves.

36:34.900 --> 36:36.983
- I think we all want
you back on our radar.

36:37.990 --> 36:40.570
- All of this has been
a wake-up call for us.

36:40.570 --> 36:44.330
This is part of the reason why
we asked Chef Ramsey to come,

36:44.330 --> 36:45.610
to help us.

36:45.610 --> 36:48.595
We're listening, we heard
everything that you had to say,

36:48.595 --> 36:52.350
and we are gonna try to
do much, much better.

36:52.350 --> 36:53.660
We're hearing you.

36:53.660 --> 36:57.290
I don't think that I knew
how the business community

36:57.290 --> 36:58.670
was connected.

36:58.670 --> 37:01.570
That everybody is feeding
off of each other.

37:01.570 --> 37:04.810
We have to realise that, to
be a part of this connection,

37:04.810 --> 37:05.883
we have to change.

37:07.965 --> 37:10.510
(upbeat music)

37:10.510 --> 37:12.550
- [Gordon] With Brent and
Afni committing to change,

37:12.550 --> 37:15.020
my team moved forward,
getting rid of all the dust

37:15.020 --> 37:16.430
and cobwebs.

37:16.430 --> 37:19.110
We furnished all the rooms
with brand new bedding,

37:19.110 --> 37:22.890
but the biggest change was
overhauling the ice cream parlour.

37:22.890 --> 37:23.723
Off you go.

37:23.723 --> 37:24.701
Ladies, welcome.

37:24.701 --> 37:26.785
(Afni gasping)

37:26.785 --> 37:27.765
- [Afni] My

37:27.765 --> 37:28.598
God!

37:29.624 --> 37:30.980
Holy

37:30.980 --> 37:31.813
moly!

37:31.813 --> 37:32.912
- Wow!

37:32.912 --> 37:34.310
Unbelievable.

37:34.310 --> 37:35.890
- Unbelievable!

37:35.890 --> 37:37.720
- [Gordon] This is what I call a parlour.

37:37.720 --> 37:39.440
You had a dreadful space here.

37:39.440 --> 37:40.820
- [Afni] Yes, oh, my God.

37:40.820 --> 37:44.120
- [Gordon] Now, it's turned
into something magical.

37:44.120 --> 37:45.130
- You think that there's any chance

37:45.130 --> 37:47.130
that I could get a sample?

37:47.130 --> 37:50.003
- We will be throwing
samples out everywhere.

37:51.249 --> 37:54.332
- [Brent] This is way
beyond our expectation.

37:54.332 --> 37:57.020
(gentle music)

37:57.020 --> 37:59.430
- Given the importance
of the local wineries,

37:59.430 --> 38:00.900
I brought in sommelier, Dave Foss.

38:00.900 --> 38:01.840
- How are you?

38:01.840 --> 38:04.080
- [Gordon] Who repaired the
bad reputations with the locals

38:04.080 --> 38:05.860
that Brent and Afni had.

38:05.860 --> 38:08.061
- You're gonna need to
nurture those relationships.

38:08.061 --> 38:08.894
- Right.

38:08.894 --> 38:10.300
- [Gordon] And he created a brand new menu

38:10.300 --> 38:12.310
featuring all Washington wine.

38:12.310 --> 38:14.540
- You're no longer gonna have to say,

38:14.540 --> 38:16.882
sorry, I don't have any local wines.

38:16.882 --> 38:18.650
- And finally, to accompany all of this,

38:18.650 --> 38:20.550
I created a smaller, more exciting menu

38:20.550 --> 38:22.960
that features all fresh food.

38:22.960 --> 38:23.793
Dig in.

38:23.793 --> 38:24.940
Have a little taste.

38:24.940 --> 38:26.630
- [Afni] Oh, my God, this is so good.

38:26.630 --> 38:27.620
- [Shelli] It's delicious.

38:27.620 --> 38:29.320
- [Teddy] Oh, my gosh!

38:29.320 --> 38:31.270
- [Afni] Everything fresh and better.

38:31.270 --> 38:32.520
- [Brent] It's fantastic.

38:33.660 --> 38:35.640
- [Gordon] What I have
learned from this community

38:35.640 --> 38:37.720
is that local support is everything.

38:37.720 --> 38:39.610
And this town is willing to give Brent

38:39.610 --> 38:41.640
and Afni a second chance.

38:41.640 --> 38:43.780
- Hi, everybody, how are you today?

38:43.780 --> 38:44.613
- Good to see you guys.

38:44.613 --> 38:48.010
- Would you like to see my
new ice cream parlour here?

38:48.010 --> 38:49.660
- [Gordon] With all the new improvements,

38:49.660 --> 38:51.950
I'm hoping Brent and Afni
make a good impression

38:51.950 --> 38:53.861
for the people of Chelan.

38:53.861 --> 38:54.694
- [Woman] I actually brought you a list

38:54.694 --> 38:56.620
of a lot of the purveyors
that we work with.

38:56.620 --> 38:57.453
- [Brent] Cool.

38:57.453 --> 38:59.780
- [Afni] Oh, you wanna check in!

38:59.780 --> 39:01.363
How are you, guys?

39:02.570 --> 39:03.693
- [Gordon] The hotel is booked up.

39:03.693 --> 39:05.410
- [Guest] This is just gorgeous.

39:05.410 --> 39:07.110
- [Gordon] And the guests
will sleep well tonight

39:07.110 --> 39:10.460
in the brand new bedding
we've added to all the rooms.

39:10.460 --> 39:11.933
- All right.

39:11.933 --> 39:13.330
- I'm gonna try the farro salad.

39:13.330 --> 39:15.030
- [Gordon] There's a real
buzz about the new menu.

39:15.030 --> 39:15.863
- [Waitress] Order up!

39:15.863 --> 39:18.030
- [Gordon] And the kitchen is
easily executing the dishes.

39:18.030 --> 39:19.450
- A quiche,

39:19.450 --> 39:21.593
a chicken sandwich, and I got the salmon.

39:23.280 --> 39:24.113
- What we're trying to do

39:24.113 --> 39:26.770
is just focus on the local wineries.

39:26.770 --> 39:28.810
- [Gordon] With the help
of sommelier, Dave Foss,

39:28.810 --> 39:30.600
the customers are pleased
with the local selection

39:30.600 --> 39:33.270
of wines that they're
offering at B.C. MacDonald's.

39:33.270 --> 39:34.966
- You like that?
- It's really good.

39:34.966 --> 39:36.133
- [Dave] Yeah?

39:37.190 --> 39:39.040
- I'm always making a mess.

39:39.040 --> 39:40.070
That's the idea.

39:40.070 --> 39:41.610
- [Brent] I'm the official scooper.

39:41.610 --> 39:43.740
- [Gordon] The ice cream shop is a hit.

39:43.740 --> 39:46.620
And Brent is even happy
giving away samples.

39:46.620 --> 39:48.720
- If you drop it on the floor, you own it.

39:49.730 --> 39:50.690
- Brent.

39:50.690 --> 39:52.290
With everything a success,

39:52.290 --> 39:54.680
I'm hoping Brent makes
one important rule change

39:54.680 --> 39:55.780
with his hotel.

39:55.780 --> 39:57.870
Have you thought about what I
mentioned about the children?

39:57.870 --> 39:59.970
Regarding children in the hotel

39:59.970 --> 40:01.490
or are you still sticking
with no children?

40:01.490 --> 40:02.323
- You know what?

40:02.323 --> 40:03.893
I'm gonna stick to the adults only.

40:03.893 --> 40:04.726
- Adults only?

40:05.990 --> 40:07.090
Why?

40:07.090 --> 40:08.093
- Well, look,

40:08.988 --> 40:10.880
when you take two or three
or four children up there,

40:10.880 --> 40:12.010
and I'm gonna tell you,

40:12.010 --> 40:14.370
they'd wipe out the whole damn place.

40:14.370 --> 40:15.640
- What, the noise?

40:15.640 --> 40:17.523
- Noise, crying, whatever.

40:18.780 --> 40:20.460
Gum and

40:20.460 --> 40:23.900
pop, and, God forbid, samples
of ice cream, they will-

40:23.900 --> 40:25.820
- You have a young daughter.

40:25.820 --> 40:28.510
- I know, I'm talking three,
four, eight year olds.

40:28.510 --> 40:30.193
- Have you asked yourself
the consequences,

40:30.193 --> 40:31.340
what am I missing on turnover?

40:31.340 --> 40:32.173
Revenue?

40:32.173 --> 40:33.290
- We may miss a few,

40:33.290 --> 40:35.050
but I think we'd miss
a few on the other end

40:35.050 --> 40:38.070
if there were two or three
kids running down the hall.

40:38.070 --> 40:40.400
- But not every kid

40:40.400 --> 40:42.130
is that noisy.

40:42.130 --> 40:44.810
I mean, just try to be open
with maybe a couple rooms.

40:44.810 --> 40:46.610
- I will give it thought.

40:46.610 --> 40:47.560
That's a tough one.

40:50.360 --> 40:52.550
- I'm disappointed Brent
won't alter his rules

40:52.550 --> 40:54.750
about allowing kids at the hotel.

40:54.750 --> 40:57.860
But hopefully, after seeing
the success of the relaunch,

40:57.860 --> 40:59.140
he'll change his mind.

40:59.140 --> 41:00.560
Keep up the good work, yes?

41:00.560 --> 41:02.320
Brian, do not let him go back.

41:02.320 --> 41:03.153
- Absolutely not.

41:03.153 --> 41:04.670
- Okay, well done.

41:04.670 --> 41:05.503
Thank you.

41:06.710 --> 41:07.543
- [Afni] Are you leaving?

41:07.543 --> 41:08.580
- Yes, I am.

41:08.580 --> 41:11.530
Everybody now in this
town is rallying around

41:11.530 --> 41:12.640
for your success.

41:12.640 --> 41:13.473
- Yes.

41:13.473 --> 41:14.540
- So embrace it.

41:14.540 --> 41:16.830
Watching you stand behind that counter

41:16.830 --> 41:18.000
just giving samples out

41:18.000 --> 41:19.600
and seeing the delight on the kids' face,

41:19.600 --> 41:20.730
that was extraordinary.
- It's awesome.

41:20.730 --> 41:22.310
- [Gordon] Please, don't go back.

41:22.310 --> 41:23.233
Stay strong.

41:23.233 --> 41:24.066
- We will.
- Oh, yeah.

41:24.066 --> 41:26.438
- There's an amazing guy
underneath all those layers.

41:26.438 --> 41:27.271
- There is?

41:27.271 --> 41:28.770
- Yes, there is, there is.

41:28.770 --> 41:29.640
- Thank you.
- There is.

41:29.640 --> 41:30.870
- You can do this, okay?

41:30.870 --> 41:31.703
- [Brent] I can do it.

41:31.703 --> 41:32.933
- Yeah, take care.
- Thank you so much.

41:32.933 --> 41:34.766
- [Gordon] All right, look after him.

41:34.766 --> 41:35.599
- Thank you so much.

41:35.599 --> 41:37.420
- And he's gonna think about
getting some kids in here.

41:37.420 --> 41:38.783
- Okay.

41:38.783 --> 41:39.881
- They're not that bad.
- We're working on it.

41:39.881 --> 41:41.332
- [Afni] I'm serious.

41:41.332 --> 41:43.160
- Mr. Stubborn.

41:43.160 --> 41:45.190
Couple scoops of ice
cream goes a long way.

41:45.190 --> 41:46.630
- Oh, boy, it's really
gone down, hasn't it?

41:46.630 --> 41:48.305
Got any money in the till yet?

41:48.305 --> 41:49.345
Thank you!

41:49.345 --> 41:50.178
- Take care.

41:50.178 --> 41:51.343
- Good night.
- Okay, bye, bye.

41:57.439 --> 42:00.700
(bouncy music)

42:00.700 --> 42:02.140
- [Gordon] Despite my
help with the outreach

42:02.140 --> 42:02.990
or the community,

42:03.910 --> 42:06.193
Brent quickly reverted
back to his old ways,

42:07.160 --> 42:09.023
distancing himself from the locals.

42:10.020 --> 42:12.980
Much of the staff have left or been fired,

42:12.980 --> 42:15.410
and the hotel's reputation within the town

42:15.410 --> 42:17.160
has only gotten worse.

42:17.160 --> 42:18.787
- Fuck.

42:18.787 --> 42:19.720
I don't know.

42:19.720 --> 42:21.663
I don't know where in
the hell everybody's at.

42:56.967 --> 42:59.717
- [Child] One potato, two potato.
